</section>
</div>
<a class="anchor" id="posts"></a>
<section class="posts">
  <h2>Posts</h2>
  <ul>
    <% blog.articles.each do |post| %>
      <li class="post-item">
        <%= link_to(post.title, post.url)%>
      </li>
      <p id='date'><%= post.date.strftime('%B %d, %Y') %></p>
    <% end %>
  </ul>
</section>
<a class="anchor" id="projects"></a>
<section class="projects">
  <h2>Some Projects</h2>
  <div class="grid-items">
    <a href="http://www.4life.com/bringdreamshome" class="grid-item">
    <div class="hover-tile-outer bringdreamshome">
      <div class="hover-tile-container">
        <div class="hover-tile hover-tile-visible">
        </div>
        <div class="hover-tile hover-tile-hidden">
          <h4>4Life Bring Dreams Home Convention 2015</h4>
          <p>4Life's convention information and registration site.</p>
          <p>Plugged into an old .Net Web Forms project for multiple language and CMS support. Fully responsive and mobile friendly with fun things like parallax, animations, and full-screen video.</p>
          <p>I designed and developed it primarily with Sass and CoffeeScript.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </a>
    <a href="http://www.fastbar.co" class="grid-item">
    <div class="hover-tile-outer fastbar">
      <div class="hover-tile-container">
        <div class="hover-tile hover-tile-visible">
        </div>
        <div class="hover-tile hover-tile-hidden">
          <h4>Fastbar</h4>
          <p>Redesign Seattle Startup Weekend - 3rd Place Winner</p>
          <p>FastBar is an event process improvement company combining iOS, Rails, and RFID technologies.</p>
          <p>I engineered the back end, from the registration system to the data analytics. I worked closely with the iOS developer integrating the native POS application with the web app and database, and worked with the designers on making it all look great.</p>
          <p>Most of the action happens on the iOS side, but check out the code on my Github to see how it all works.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </a>
    <a href="http://beautilist.herokuapp.com" class="grid-item">
      <div class="hover-tile-outer beautilist">
        <div class="hover-tile-container">
          <div class="hover-tile hover-tile-visible">
          </div>
          <div class="hover-tile hover-tile-hidden">
            <h4>Beautilist</h4>
            <p>Beautilist is a Rails app built in 4 days that implements a tree data structure in Ruby to infinitely nest lists and uses Ajax calls to manipulate the lists and their children around the DOM in real-time.</p>
            <p>Sign up to add as many lists and sublists as you want to see what the app is capable of.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </a>
    <a href="http://codeunion2.herokuapp.com" class="grid-item">
    <div class="hover-tile-outer codeunion">
